<br>
Can someone also explain the bonus that now applies to armour please, does this affect non-casters?<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udaleb123.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daleb123</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 154<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(7/8/02 5:12:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1679.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Damage Bonus</span><hr size=1> The Damage Bonus is an amount ADDED to each hit with your primary hand, for melee and hybrid classes only. The Damage rating on a weapon, on the other hand, is a damage MULTIPLIER. The easiest way I can explain it is by giving a fairly accurate formula for max damage for Level 1-50 (for all classes):<br>
<br>
Max Damage = [(STR + weapon skill + ATK buffs)/100]*DMG + Damage Bonus<br>
<br>
DMG = the Damage rating listed on the weapon<br>
<br>
There is a minimum value formula of 2*DMG + 1.<br>
<br>
There are Damage Caps in place for lower levels that I won't explain here unless you want me to - they are not relevant for answering this question.<br>
<br>
Notice that STR, skill, and DMG (and ATK buffs) act as multipliers in the formula, while Damage Bonus adds. Because Damage Bonus ADDS to each hit, getting this more frequently actually increases Damage/time output. This is why low delay becomes more important for damage output at higher levels. <br>
<br>
Since the Damage Bonus is added after your opponent's Damage Mitigation is determined, it also raises your MINIMUM damage hit, but again only for the primary hand.<br>
<br>
For 1-handed weapons (including fists), Damage Bonus = (Level-25)/3. For 2-handed weapons, the bonus varies by the Delay of the weapon as well as the Level of the wielder, so that slower weapons have larger delays.<br>
<br>
Does that help? <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showPrevMessage?topicID=1679.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showNextMessage?topicID=1679.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1679.topic&index=1><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.emailToFriend?topicID=1679.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.threadControl?topicID=1679.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1679.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1679.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="monklybusiness43508frm13">Board Rules<option value="monklybusiness43508frm17">Monk Change<option value="monklybusiness43508frm1">General<option value="monklybusiness43508frm16">New Features<option value="monklybusiness43508frm2">Guides and Tact